sorcer.core.context.node

Class ContextNode

  • java.lang.Object
    • sorcer.core.context.node.ContextNode
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Serializable

    public class ContextNode
extends Object
implements Serializable
    The class ContextNode is a wrapper for externally persisted data, for example in files or databases. The data is exposed via references called "data items" that can be used as arguments to a setters (setItemValue) and getter (getItemValue) in externally persisted data.
    See Also:
